<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1058,350,431]" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">
D i a g n o s i s: Only in specimens of this 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1950" box="[639,763,350,371]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[639,763,350,371]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">Pujoliclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species do the elytra show brown spots amidst an otherwise yellow disc. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1950" box="[738,862,379,400]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[738,862,379,400]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">Pujoliclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
PIC was revised in 2014 (
<bibRefCitation author="OPITZ W" box="[216,351,409,431]" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019" pagination="727 - 756" refId="ref53564" refString="OPITZ W. (2014 d): Classification, natural history, and evolution of the checkered beetle genus Pujoliclerus PIC (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Peloniinae). - The Coleopteristss Bulletin 68 (4): 727 - 756." type="journal article" year="2014">OPITZ 2014d</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1059,446,644]" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 
<quantity box="[516,597,446,468]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[673,753,446,468]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,446,468]" captionStart="Figs 350-353" captionStartId="115.[151,191,1511,1533]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,200,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@115.[153,1061,200,1498]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="Figs 350-353: Habitus; (350) Pujoliclerus tuxtlas; (351) P. variolus; (352) Sicamus suprus; (353) Sirpa acara." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746838" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746838/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">Fig. 351</figureCitation>
. Color: Forebody, pterothorax, legs and abdomen yellow; antenna brown. Head: Antenna (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 61-91" captionStartId="73.[151,191,1343,1365]" captionTargetBox="[151,1033,198,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@73.[151,1059,198,1328]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figs 61-91: Antennae; (61) Madoniella muralla; (62) M. nota; (63) M. acicula; (64) M. aspera; (65) M. baja; (66) M. delta; (67) Amboakis bermejo; (68) Pujoliclerus variolus; (69) Megatrachys irrasis; (70) Cregya arima; (71) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (72) Cregya vicosa; (73) Pujoliclerus abditus; (74) P. dexus; (75) Cregya triguttula; (76) Pyticeroides brevitubulus; (77) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (78) Cregya biguttula; (79) Sirpa acara; (80) Parapelonides naranjo; (81) Cregya livida; (82) Amboakis collucoatis; (83) Ampleris jatai; (84) Megaphloeus yasuni; (85) Pelonium implacide, male; (86) Epiphloeus prolixicornus; (87) Pelonium implacide, female; (88) Epiphloeus mantillerii; (89) Amboakis mitaraka; (90) Ellipotoma makrosa; (91) Cregya maura." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746752/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
) capitate, 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[309,322,501,515]" fontSize="6" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">th</superScript>
antennomere expanded, capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 triangular, antennomere 10 ovoid; eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye as wide as frons (EW/FW 25/25). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[448,541,563,585]" captionStart="Figs 153-162" captionStartId="78.[151,191,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[174,1045,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@78.[153,1061,200,1429]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Figs 153-162: Pronota; (153) Agnatis vaurieae; (154) Pelonium atrigonatium; (155) Pujoliclerus variolus; (156) Epiphloeus prolixicornus; (157) Sirpa latiflava; (158) Neorthopleura turnbowi; (159) Aphelocerus yaguare; (160) A. copanus; (161) Amboakis mitaraka; (162) Ellipotoma makrosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746762/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
) quadrate (PW/PL 70/70), disc finely punctate, lateral tubercle well developed; elytral asetiferous punctures restricted to humeral region (EL/EW 175/65). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform.
</paragraph>
