<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1058,763,815]" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[562,645,763,784]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">variolus</emphasis>
, is a Latin adjective that stems from 
<emphasis box="[151,224,793,814]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="1019">variola</emphasis>
(= spotted); with regards to the coloration of the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
